casebody.data:
PETER D. STRAUCH, et al., Respondents, v. CATHARINE WARREN, Appellant.

Before Speir and Freedman, JJ.

Decided June 6, 1881. Appeal from judgment and from an order denying: a motion for a new trial upon the minutes. S. F. Kneeland, for appellant. George W. Lord, for respondents. Opinion per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed, with costs.
